This function looks like it creates three buffers -- `hashbuf`, `hashbuf_slice`, and within `read_hash_bytes`, it creates another `hashbytes`.

This happens a lot when `read_hash_bytes` is called: I suspect we could eliminate the need for `fast_extend_from_slice` on a majority of reads by changing the signature (or creating a new function) for `read_hash_bytes` to:

```rust
pub fn read_hash_bytes<F: Read + Seek>(f: &mut F, buf: &mut [u8; 32]) -> Result<(), Error> {
    f.read(buf)
        .map_err(Error::IOError)?;
    
    Ok(())
}
```

